name: Uma Batukaru
address: Jl. Beji Sudamala Sanggulan, Banjar Anyar, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82121, Indonesia
review 1:
Great place next to some rice fields in Kediri. üåæ Underrated and little known to non-locals at the time of posting.
But the place has great music and good food. I had the Terbawa Rasa Pizza personal size - delicious, and I would go back for more. üçï
But for certain, it's finding this place in the middle of seemingly nowhere that makes it so great.
Uma Batukaru is a local hidden gem. üíé
review 2: Amazing restaurant surrounded by ride fields. I fed myself and 2 others, with a bottle of spirit and dessert for 35 bucks.
review 3: Hidden gem in the city of tabanan, great paddyfield view, spacious place, they also have live music, and also kids club.
review 4:
I was around on Tabanan city and looking for a place to have lunch. I'm glad that I choose to have lunch here! I was ordering strawberry coffee mocktail (unique taste and good, and a very cute glass!). And for the meal I was trying nasi ayam bakar and ayam kuah pedas (it's ok spicy, good for tummy). The access to the place was interesting too. Feels like adventuring. Good for the belly sensation before the lunch.
Overall, a good place to visit, friendly to pocket and good for lunch. I heard that they do live music on weekend too, def will check it.
review 5: Place was great, food not really good,
